1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:02,889
In 1940, the Tacoma Narrows Bridge looked

2
00:00:02,889 --> 00:00:05,600
like the future. It was long,

3
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:07,974
slender, cheaper than the original

4
00:00:07,974 --> 00:00:10,921
conservative design, and beautiful enough

5
00:00:10,921 --> 00:00:12,804
to make its movement famous.

6
00:00:13,727 --> 00:00:16,554
People called it Galloping Gertie.

7
00:00:16,554 --> 00:00:19,125
But the wind on collapse day was

8
00:00:19,125 --> 00:00:21,835
not extraordinary. The bridge had already

9
00:00:21,835 --> 00:00:23,925
survived stronger autumn winds.

10
00:00:23,925 --> 00:00:26,402
The hidden problem was what the bridge

11
00:00:26,402 --> 00:00:28,338
did to the air after it started

12
00:00:28,338 --> 00:00:30,816
moving. Its shallow solid plate-girder

13
00:00:30,816 --> 00:00:32,906
deck was too flexible in torsion.

14
00:00:32,906 --> 00:00:35,110
Once the roadway began to twist,

15
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:37,333
the motion changed the airflow,

16
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,898
and the changed airflow fed the next

17
00:00:39,898 --> 00:00:43,262
twist. Engineers were studying the motion,

18
00:00:43,262 --> 00:00:45,066
but the design culture had not yet

19
00:00:45,066 --> 00:00:47,386
made dynamic aerodynamic testing routine

20
00:00:47,386 --> 00:00:48,546
for bridges like this.

21
00:00:49,670 --> 00:00:51,173
The bridge did not just meet wind.

22
00:00:52,036 --> 00:00:53,797
It entered a behavior its own design

23
00:00:53,797 --> 00:00:57,679
made possible. Small causes, massive

24
00:00:57,679 --> 00:00:58,792
consequences.
